Clean
=====

Clean action runs only in server mode and it executes garbage collector, removes temporary files, log files and also removes the cache objects.

The standard command line is described below:
areasy -action clean [-olderthan <10|20|..(in days)>] [-force]

Where:
	-force     = Force to remove all objects from the cache layer. Otherwise will remove only expired objects.

	-olderthan = Specify a period (in days) that will be considered to remove the log files and also the temporary files.


Examples:
---------
1) areasy -action clean
	= removes all expired objects from cache

2) areasy -action clean -force
	= removes all objects from cache

3) areasy -action clean -olderthan 3
	= removes all expired objects from cache and all log and related file older than 3 days
